article.headline: Arkansas St. 63, North Texas 47
article.story: JONESBORO, Ark. -- Martavius Adams had 16 points and 13 rebounds to lead Arkansas State to a 63-47 victory against fading North Texas on Thursday night. Donald Boone scored 12 points and Edward Townsel 10 for the Red Wolves (16-14, 10-5 Sun Belt), who remained in a tie for first in the conference's West Division with Louisiana-Lafayette, which beat Denver in overtime on Thursday. George Odufuwa had 12 points and 14 rebounds for North Texas (17-10, 6-8), which has lost six of its last seven, putting a 13-2 start -- the Mean Green's best since 1952-53 -- further in the rearview mirror. North Texas committed a season-high 20 turnovers, and giveaways on three consecutive possessions sparked an 11-1 Arkansas State run that gave the Red Wolves a 47-40 advantage with eight minutes to play. For the first time in 30 games, North Texas could not hold a halftime lead. It was up 26-25 at intermission but shot just 27.3 percent (6 for 22) from the floor in the second half.
